JOHANNESBURG - The creator of Madiba, the African Opera, Unathi Mtirara has died.
	
	A close family friend said he was rushed to hospital after he complained of chest pains on Friday night. Funeral arrangements are under way. His body is expected to be laid to rest in the Eastern Cape. READ: Chris Hani's life story told through opera Mtirara is also Nelson Mandela's great nephew and a member of the Abathembu Royal Family. He’ll be remembered for both the controversy and a historical legacy of the opera in Madiba's name. Mtirara is survived by his opera singer wife Nonhlanhla and his daughter. eNCA